WEBVTT

00:05.339 --> 00:07.406
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SPIKE, THIS BOMB COULD GO</i>
<i> AT ANY MOMENT.</i>

00:07.408 --> 00:08.640
BUDDY, WHAT'RE YOU DOING?

00:08.642 --> 00:09.441
SPIKE, GET IN THE HARNESS.

00:09.443 --> 00:10.542
G, A-B-C,

00:10.544 --> 00:12.578
D-E-F-G, G IS FOUR.

00:12.580 --> 00:15.280
PARKER:
SPIKE! THERE'S NO TIME,
YOU GET OUTTA THERE!

00:15.282 --> 00:17.316
A! A IS... A'S TWO,
AM I RIGHT?

00:17.318 --> 00:18.617
FOUR, 2. L.

00:18.619 --> 00:19.618
SPIKE!

00:19.620 --> 00:21.487
ED, GET OUTTA HERE!

00:21.489 --> 00:24.256
EDDIE, YOU GET OUTTA THERE
RIGHT NOW DAMMIT!

00:24.258 --> 00:25.674
RIGHT NOW!

00:25.675 --> 00:27.091
60 SECONDS.
I'M NOT LEAVING HIM DOWN THERE.

00:27.094 --> 00:28.460
ED, ONE MINUTE
DOWN RANGE.

00:29.397 --> 00:30.462
SPIKE...

00:38.339 --> 00:39.405
SPIKE...

00:40.408 --> 00:42.041
HELP ME!

00:42.043 --> 00:43.108
HELP ME.

00:48.349 --> 00:49.815
(ROTORS BEAT)

00:57.525 --> 01:00.325
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> DARK DAYS FOR JUEVENTUS,</i>
<i> DAD.</i>

01:00.327 --> 01:02.461
THREE LOSSES IN A ROW.

01:02.463 --> 01:05.230
TOO MUCH OLD
IN THE OLD LADY.

01:05.232 --> 01:07.833
THEY ONLY SCORED TWO GOALS
IN THEIR LAST FOUR GAMES.

01:07.835 --> 01:11.637
MAYBE IF THEY PLAYED
MORE MEN BACK OF CENTRE...?

01:11.639 --> 01:14.573
IT'S ABOUT KNOWING
WHERE YOU NEED TO BE.

01:14.575 --> 01:17.643
IF YOU TAKE CHANCES,
EVERYONE ENDS UP PAYING.

01:20.114 --> 01:21.380
YOU...

01:21.382 --> 01:23.415
(DRY, WHEEZED COUGH)

01:24.351 --> 01:25.250
'KAY, BA.

01:25.252 --> 01:27.586
'KAY HAVE SOME WATER, BA.

01:27.588 --> 01:30.722
BA. 'KAY, I'LL BE BACK
IN A SECOND, OKAY?

01:30.724 --> 01:31.757
<i> NURSE!</i>

01:31.759 --> 01:33.292
(COUGHING)

01:33.294 --> 01:34.760
SPIKE:
NURSE!

01:38.199 --> 01:40.599
NURSE SAYS HE JUST NEEDS
SOME REST. OKAY?

01:40.601 --> 01:42.434
HE'LL BE BETTER ONCE
WE GET HIM BACK HOME.

01:42.436 --> 01:44.670
YEAH, DOCTOR JAMAL SAID
IT SHOULD BE TONIGHT.

01:44.672 --> 01:45.871
OKAY, GREAT THEN.
ALL RIGHT.

01:45.873 --> 01:47.172
I GOT MY PHONE.

01:47.174 --> 01:50.609
PROMISE ME, DON'T MENTION
JUEVENTUS.

01:50.611 --> 01:51.610
SAY "BYE" FOR ME.

01:51.612 --> 01:52.678
OKAY.

01:53.647 --> 01:54.847
(MONITOR BUTTONS BEEP)

01:58.519 --> 02:00.586
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> TEAM ONE, FIRE AND POLICE</i>
<i> ARE ON ROUTE</i>

02:00.588 --> 02:02.521
<i> AND WILL MEET YOU</i>
<i> AT FAIRBANKS TOWER SQUARE.</i>

02:02.523 --> 02:04.106
OKAY, TEAM,
HERE'S WHAT WE KNOW

02:04.107 --> 02:05.690
FROM THE GOOD FOLKS
AT FAIRBANKS TOWER.

02:05.693 --> 02:08.260
A SUSPICIOUS PACKAGE WAS
FOUND ON THE LOWER LEVEL

02:08.262 --> 02:09.394
OF THE NORTH TOWER -

02:09.396 --> 02:10.913
<i> CORNER OF KING AND BAY.</i>

02:10.914 --> 02:12.431
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SECURITY GUARD WAS ON PATROL,</i>

02:12.433 --> 02:14.199
<i> SEES SOMETHING IN A TRASH CAN</i>
<i> HE DOESN'T LIKE,</i>

02:14.201 --> 02:15.234
AND HE CALLS IT IN.

02:15.236 --> 02:16.568
SO WHAT WAS THE PACKAGE?

02:16.570 --> 02:18.737
ED:
BLUE AND WHITE VINYL GYM BAG.

02:18.739 --> 02:20.239
<i> HE OPENED IT UP,</i>
<i> SAW SOME WIRES,</i>

02:20.241 --> 02:21.306
<i> DIDN'T GO ANY FURTHER.</i>

02:21.308 --> 02:22.674
WOW, VINYL GYM BAGS.

02:22.676 --> 02:24.243
I HAVEN'T SEEN ONE OF
THOSE SINCE HIGH SCHOOL.

02:24.245 --> 02:26.212
HEY, I HAD ONE OF THOSE.

02:26.213 --> 02:28.180
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> OKAY, GUYS, LET'S CHECK OUT</i>
<i> THE PACKAGE,</i>

02:28.182 --> 02:29.548
<i> LET US KNOW WHAT'S GOING ON.</i>

02:29.550 --> 02:31.517
SAM, GO WITH 'EM,
NORTH EAST DOOR -

02:31.519 --> 02:32.718
GIVE OUR GUYS SOME
PRIVACY.

02:32.720 --> 02:33.719
WE'LL STAY ON THE STREET,

02:33.721 --> 02:35.387
COORDINATE WITH FIRE
JUST IN CASE.

02:35.389 --> 02:36.788
COPY THAT.

02:36.790 --> 02:39.358
BUILDING MANAGEMENT SAID
THEY SHUT DOWN THE H-VAC

02:39.360 --> 02:41.226
<i> JUST IN CASE</i>
<i> IT'S A BIO-HAZARD.</i>

02:41.228 --> 02:42.794
JUST TAKE A LOOK INSIDE,
BUTTON IT DOWN,

02:42.796 --> 02:45.364
<i> AND LET'S GET BACK HOME.</i>

02:58.546 --> 03:00.546
RAF:
A LOT OF TROUBLE TO GO
THROUGH FOR A GYM BAG.

03:00.547 --> 03:02.547
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> YEAH, WE GET A COUPLE</i>
<i> OF THESE CALLS A YEAR -</i>

03:02.550 --> 03:03.815
USUALLY IT'S NOTHING.

03:03.817 --> 03:05.884
BABYCAKES, WE HAVEN'T
HAD A DATE FOR A WHILE.

03:05.886 --> 03:07.219
SEE THAT YELLOW BOX ON HER?

03:07.221 --> 03:08.787
MM-HM.
AT'S A NEW MULTI-RAE
US -

03:08.789 --> 03:10.656
GIVES HER A NOSE
LIKE A DOBERMAN.

03:10.658 --> 03:13.458
10 PPM OF 35 DIFFERENT
DEADLY CHEMICALS, RIGHT?

03:13.460 --> 03:14.793
BUDDY. NICE.

03:14.795 --> 03:15.878
BUT YOUR ORDER
OF MAGNITUDE.

03:15.879 --> 03:16.962
YOU GOTTA MOVE
THE DECIMAL PLACE.

03:16.964 --> 03:18.797
ONE PART PER MILLION
AND SHE BARKS.

03:18.799 --> 03:20.732
DON'T SELL MY BABY SHORT.

03:20.734 --> 03:21.800
MY BAD.

03:21.802 --> 03:23.735
CONTACT INFO
ON ALL OUR TENANTS.

03:23.737 --> 03:25.204
CLEARING THE BUILDING NOW.

03:25.205 --> 03:26.672
NICE. LOOKS LIKE YOU'VE
DONE THIS BEFORE.

03:26.674 --> 03:28.340
THAT'S WHAT THE DRILLS
ARE FOR.

03:28.342 --> 03:29.808
WE GET ALMOST EVERYONE OUT.

03:29.810 --> 03:31.843
YEAH, "ALMOST EVERYONE"
DOESN'T REALLY CUT IT.

03:31.845 --> 03:33.612
H.
THANKS.

03:34.582 --> 03:35.914
OH! THANK GOD
YOU'RE HERE.

03:35.916 --> 03:36.982
I KEEP TELLING THEM
TO GET OUT.

03:36.984 --> 03:38.617
BUT THEY WON'T LEAVE.

03:38.619 --> 03:40.485
HEY!

03:40.487 --> 03:44.823
POLICE! WE NEED YOU TO CLEAR
THIS AREA IMMEDIATELY.

03:45.759 --> 03:47.276
WHAT'S THE PROTOCOL?

03:47.277 --> 03:48.794
INVESTIGATE. EVALUATE.
NEUTRALIZE.

03:48.796 --> 03:50.662
HOPEFULLY NOT DETONATE.

03:50.664 --> 03:52.898
LET'S SEE WHAT SHE SMELLS.

03:57.271 --> 03:59.905
CLEAR THIS ROOM NOW.
YOU'RE BEING EVACUATED.

03:59.907 --> 04:01.707
FOR ANOTHER FIRE DRILL?
NO WAY!

04:01.709 --> 04:03.642
I'M NOT ASKING YOU,
MA'AM.

04:03.643 --> 04:05.576
GOOD, 'CAUSE I'M NOT AGREEING.
SAM: HEY!

04:05.577 --> 04:07.510
IT'S WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.
THEY WON'T OPEN THE DOOR.

04:07.514 --> 04:09.414
I'LL OPEN IT FOR THEM.

04:10.618 --> 04:12.684
SPIKE.
I FOUND YOUR BAG.

04:12.686 --> 04:14.553
<i> YOU MUST HAVE WALKED</i>
<i> RIGHT PAST IT.</i>

04:14.555 --> 04:15.721
UH, WE'RE WITH
THE PACKAGE NOW.

04:15.723 --> 04:17.689
(SCANNER BEEPS)

04:17.691 --> 04:19.291
SAM, GET THOSE PEOPLE
OUT OF HERE RIGHT NOW!

04:19.293 --> 04:21.043
<i> THERE'S TWO BOMBS.</i>

04:21.044 --> 04:22.794
SIR,
STEP AROUND THE CORNER.

04:24.765 --> 04:26.398
(GUNSHOT POPS,
WORKERS SCREAM AND YELP)

04:26.400 --> 04:27.799
(GLASS SHATTERS)

04:28.802 --> 04:30.469
EVERYBODY GET OUTTA HERE NOW!

04:30.471 --> 04:31.603
(BEEPING)

04:32.539 --> 04:34.273
SPIKE: RDX.
RAF: ACTIVE EXPLOSIVE.

04:34.275 --> 04:36.875
(THUNDEROUS EXPLOSION,
DEBRIS CLATTERS)

04:36.877 --> 04:38.744
(SECONDARY EXPLOSION BLASTS)

04:38.746 --> 04:40.879
PARKER:
WHAT'S GOING ON?

04:40.881 --> 04:42.981
WE GOT TWO SEPARATE
EXPLOSIONS.

04:42.983 --> 04:44.449
JULES AND I ARE GOING
DOWN NOW.

04:44.451 --> 04:46.585
SPIKE, RAF? TALK TO ME.
GET OUTTA THE WAY!

04:46.587 --> 04:48.854
SAM? SPIKE? RAF?
TALK TO ME.

04:49.790 --> 04:52.457
(ELECTRICITY FIZZLES,
MAN BREATHES HEAVILY)

04:58.465 --> 05:00.065
(WIRES CRACKLES,
COUGHING NEARBY)

05:08.409 --> 05:09.975
(HYPERVENTILATING)

05:12.579 --> 05:15.580
SAM? SAM, BUDDY?
TALK TO ME PLEASE!

05:17.685 --> 05:19.768
<i> SPIKE, RAF?</i>
<i> TALK TO ME!</i>

05:19.769 --> 05:21.852
<i> WHAT'S GOING ON?</i>
<i> YOU GUYS OKAY?</i>

05:23.324 --> 05:24.790
<i> SPIKE? RAF?</i>

05:27.594 --> 05:28.927
RAF?

05:28.929 --> 05:30.462
RAF?

05:30.464 --> 05:31.763
ARE YOU HURT?

05:31.765 --> 05:33.098
RAF? YOU HURT?

05:33.100 --> 05:35.400
YEAH, I'M GOOD MAN.
YOU? YOU OKAY?

05:35.402 --> 05:37.836
<i> SPIKE: I'M GOOD.</i>
<i> PARKER: SPIKE? RAF?</i>

05:37.838 --> 05:40.872
BOSS, IT'S SPIKE.
RAF AND I ARE OKAY.

05:40.874 --> 05:42.908
<i> THE DEVICE DETONATED.</i>

05:42.910 --> 05:44.876
THERE'S SIGNIFICANT
DAMAGE.

05:44.878 --> 05:46.611
HALLWAY'S CAVED IN.

05:46.613 --> 05:47.679
SAM?

05:47.681 --> 05:50.882
<i> SAM, TALK TO ME!</i>
<i> (WOMAN CRIES NEARBY)</i>

05:50.884 --> 05:52.050
<i> RAF?</i>

05:52.052 --> 05:53.051
GO FIND OUR GUY!

05:53.053 --> 05:54.419
RAF:
COPY THAT.

05:55.356 --> 05:56.355
(COUGHING)

05:56.357 --> 05:57.356
<i> ED:</i>
<i> SAM, YOU COPY?</i>

05:57.358 --> 05:58.423
(BOOTS CLOMP ON STAIRS)

05:59.960 --> 06:01.026
SAM?

06:01.028 --> 06:02.928
COME ON, SPEAK TO ME,
SAM.

06:02.930 --> 06:04.897
CHIEF!

06:04.898 --> 06:06.865
WE GOT A 10-66,
TWO EXPLOSIONS UNDERGROUND.

06:06.867 --> 06:08.133
LET'S WORK TOGETHER,

06:08.134 --> 06:09.400
TIGHT PERIMETER AROUND
THE PLAZA, ALL RIGHT?

06:09.403 --> 06:11.053
NO ONE GETS IN,

06:11.054 --> 06:12.704
AND WE DAMN SURE TALK
TO ANYBODY WHO COMES OUT.

06:12.706 --> 06:14.005
YOU GOT IT.

06:14.007 --> 06:16.007
RAF, YOU FIND SAM?
TALK TO ME, BUDDY.

06:16.009 --> 06:18.510
<i> RAF:</i>
<i> ON IT, BOSS,</i>
<i> BUT THERE'S A LOT OF DEBRIS.</i>

06:18.512 --> 06:19.978
<i> AND A LOT OF SMOKE.</i>

06:22.649 --> 06:23.715
SAM?

06:24.852 --> 06:26.785
SAM?

06:26.786 --> 06:28.719
HEY! I NEED EVERYONE
TO MOVE BACK TO WALL.

06:28.722 --> 06:30.055
<i> THIS COULD COME DOWN</i>
<i> ANY SECOND NOW.</i>

06:30.057 --> 06:31.757
<i> MOVE BACK, PLEASE.</i>

06:31.759 --> 06:33.992
SAM?
AW, MAN, SAM'S DOWN.

06:33.994 --> 06:34.993
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> IS HE BREATHING?</i>

06:34.995 --> 06:37.028
BOSS, I FOUND SAM.

06:37.030 --> 06:40.031
HE'S UNCONSCIOUS,
BUT HIS PULSE IS GOOD.

06:40.033 --> 06:41.666
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

06:42.603 --> 06:44.669
HOW MANY PEOPLE BACK THERE?
HOW MANY?

06:44.671 --> 06:46.505
UH, THERE'S, AH...

06:46.507 --> 06:48.006
SIX OF US.

06:48.008 --> 06:49.074
RAF: BOSS?
MAN 2: IS SHE OKAY?

06:49.076 --> 06:50.942
<i> WE'VE GOT SIX CIVILIANS.</i>

06:50.944 --> 06:51.910
<i> I'VE GOT A FEMALE,</i>
<i> SHE'S DOWN,</i>

06:51.912 --> 06:53.445
<i> BUT SHE'S BREATHING.</i>

06:53.446 --> 06:54.979
<i> SHE'S TRAPPED UNDER</i>
<i> ALL THIS DEBRIS, BOSS.</i>

06:54.982 --> 06:56.315
I CAN'T MOVE HER.

06:56.316 --> 06:57.649
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> OKAY, WE EMS COMING.</i>

06:57.651 --> 07:00.018
A GUY'S WAITING FOR YOU.
JUST STAY CLOSE, RAF.

07:00.020 --> 07:02.421
<i> ED:</i>
<i> BOSS, THIS DOESN'T LOOK GOOD.</i>

07:02.423 --> 07:03.555
I'M GONNA TRY
TO GET THROUGH.

07:03.557 --> 07:05.957
JULES, SEND THE MEDICS
DOWN MY WAY.

07:05.959 --> 07:08.093
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> NORTHEAST CORNER'S CAVED IN.</i>
<i> THERE'S NO WAY OUT.</i>

07:08.095 --> 07:09.728
<i> RAF:</i>
<i> BOSS, THERE WAS DEFINITELY</i>
<i> A SECOND EXPLOSION</i>

07:09.730 --> 07:10.646
<i> AT THE OTHER END OF THE HALL.</i>

07:10.647 --> 07:11.563
THERE'S SO MUCH DAMAGE
DOWN HERE,

07:11.565 --> 07:12.564
WE ARE TOTALLY TRAPPED.

07:12.566 --> 07:13.632
MAN:
OVER HERE, WE NEED HELP.

07:13.634 --> 07:15.534
TWO BOMBS,
TWO EXPLOSIONS...

07:16.470 --> 07:18.103
ALMOST ON TOP OF EACH OTHER.

07:18.104 --> 07:19.737
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> TWO BOMBS.</i>
<i> ALMOST SIMULTANEOUS.</i>

07:19.740 --> 07:21.840
SPIKE, WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

07:21.841 --> 07:23.941
WELL, WHAT'S THE PLAY HERE?
WHY TWO BOMBS?

07:23.944 --> 07:25.010
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> MAXIMUM DAMAGE?</i>

07:25.012 --> 07:26.678
<i> THE SECOND ONE'S A BACK UP?</i>

07:26.680 --> 07:28.980
THE BOMBS, THERE'RE BIG,
BUT NOT HUGE.

07:28.982 --> 07:30.549
<i> RAF:</i>
<i> ARE YOU OKAY BACK THERE?</i>
<i> IS EVERYONE OKAY?</i>

07:30.551 --> 07:32.551
MAN 2:
DO WE LOOK OKAY?

07:32.553 --> 07:34.519
WELL, WHAT'S WORTH TARGETING
DOWN THERE?

07:34.521 --> 07:35.754
SPIKE:
THAT'S JUST IT.

07:35.755 --> 07:36.988
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SPIKE, WHAT DO YOU MEAN?</i>

07:36.990 --> 07:38.523
IT'S MORE LIKE THEY WERE MEANT
TO SEAL THE HALLWAY

07:38.525 --> 07:41.026
THAN TO DESTROY ANYTHING
IN PARTICULAR.

07:41.028 --> 07:42.894
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> WHY?</i>

07:42.896 --> 07:45.764
THAT'S WHAT I'M TRYING
TO FIGURE OUT.

07:45.766 --> 07:47.699
(DROP BOX RATTLES)

07:47.701 --> 07:49.768
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> FORGET IT.</i>
<i>LET'S GET YOU GUYS OUTTA THERE.</i>

07:49.770 --> 07:52.504
<i> WE CAN WORRY ABOUT A MOTIVE</i>
<i> LATER.</i>

07:58.479 --> 08:00.996
(SCANNER BEEPS)

08:00.997 --> 08:03.514
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> WHERE'D YOU GO, SPIKE?</i>
<i> WHAT'S GOING ON?</i>

08:03.517 --> 08:05.116
<i> BAD NEWS, BOSS.</i>

08:05.118 --> 08:06.985
<i> THERE'S ANOTHER DEVICE.</i>

08:06.987 --> 08:09.054
<i> AND IT'S HUGE.</i>

08:09.056 --> 08:11.089
IT MAKES THE OTHER TWO
LOOK LIKE FIRECRACKERS.

08:14.595 --> 08:24.636
¶¶¶

08:24.638 --> 08:29.608
¶¶¶

08:29.610 --> 08:42.687
¶¶¶

08:48.529 --> 08:49.995
PARKER:
SPIKE, SAY AGAIN?
THERE'S ANOTHER BOMB?

08:49.997 --> 08:51.129
<i> ANOTHER GYM BAG?</i>

08:51.131 --> 08:53.148
I WISH.

08:53.149 --> 08:55.166
WE'RE LOOKING AT 50,
MAYBE 70 POUNDS OF PLASTIQUE.

08:55.168 --> 08:57.068
WITH THE HALLWAY BLOCKED UP
AFTER THE FIRST TWO,

08:57.070 --> 08:59.771
THIS THING'LL SHOOT STRAIGHT UP
LIKE A ROMAN CANDLE.

08:59.773 --> 09:01.873
THE WHOLE BUILDING COULD GO.

09:02.809 --> 09:03.842
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> DOES IT HAVE A TIMER?</i>

09:03.844 --> 09:04.910
I'M LOOKING.

09:07.748 --> 09:09.848
RAF, WHAT KIND OF INJURIES
WE HAVE DOWN THERE?

09:09.850 --> 09:12.584
MOSTLY SUPERFICIAL.
ONE'S SERIOUS.

09:12.586 --> 09:14.920
<i> SAM'S STILL UNCONSCIOUS</i>
<i> BUT HE'S BREATHING FINE.</i>

09:14.922 --> 09:17.188
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> OKAY, HELP'S ON THE WAY.</i>
<i> JUST STAND BY.</i>

09:17.190 --> 09:18.990
I'VE ORGANIZED THE UNIS,
WE'RE EVACUATING THE BUILDING,

09:18.992 --> 09:20.659
TOP DOWN,
IT SHOULD BE CLEAR, SIR.

09:20.661 --> 09:21.794
OKAY, KEEP MOVING.

09:21.795 --> 09:22.928
WE DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH TIME
WE'RE WORKING WITH.

09:26.600 --> 09:27.215
JULES:
'KAY.

09:27.216 --> 09:27.831
WINNIE'S,
WHERE'S MY COMMAND TRUCK?

09:27.834 --> 09:29.334
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> SECONDS AWAY, BOSS.</i>

09:29.336 --> 09:30.869
EDDIE, HOW ARE WE?

09:30.871 --> 09:33.038
WE ANY CLOSER TO GETTING
OUR FOLKS DOWN THERE?

09:33.040 --> 09:35.173
WE GOT A KEY STRUCTURAL WALL
HERE THAT'S BEEN DAMAGED.

09:35.175 --> 09:36.741
WE PULL OUT THE WRONG PIECE
OF RUBBLE,

09:36.743 --> 09:38.210
THE WHOLE THING'LL COME DOWN.

09:38.211 --> 09:39.678
FIRE CAPTAIN WE'LL NEED THREE,
FOUR HOURS MAYBE

09:39.680 --> 09:42.280
IF WE DON'T WANT IT ALL
CAVING IN.

09:42.282 --> 09:43.815
THREE HOURS.
WE GOT THAT LONG?

09:43.817 --> 09:45.984
SPIKE, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

09:45.986 --> 09:47.919
SPIKE:
I THINK EVERYBODY'S
MOVE GOTTA BACK RIGHT NOW.

09:47.921 --> 09:49.754
WHY, SPIKE?
WHAT DO YOU SEE?

09:49.756 --> 09:50.822
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> TIMER IS CHEMICAL.</i>

09:50.824 --> 09:52.290
I CAN'T BE EXACT, BOSS,
BUT...

09:52.292 --> 09:53.575
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> COULD YOU GIVE ME A GUESS?</i>

09:53.576 --> 09:54.859
<i> RAF:</i>
<i> COME ON, GUYS,</i>
<i> YOU GOTTA MOVE BACK.</i>

09:54.861 --> 09:56.962
<i> GIVE HIM SOME ROOM.</i>

09:56.964 --> 09:59.030
MOVE BACK!
LET US WORK!

09:59.900 --> 10:02.033
MAYBE FIVE MINUTES.

10:05.238 --> 10:06.938
JULES, LET'S CLEAR THE PLAZA.

10:06.940 --> 10:08.273
COME ON, LET'S GO!

10:09.209 --> 10:11.343
ALL RIGHT, GET UP TOP.
NOW!

10:11.345 --> 10:14.012
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i>SPIKE, CAN YOU GET INSIDE THERE</i>
<i> AND DEFUSE IT?</i>

10:14.014 --> 10:15.013
THERE'S GOTTA BE
COUNTER MEASURES.

10:15.015 --> 10:16.147
I DO ONE THING WRONG...

10:16.149 --> 10:18.483
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> AH, YEAH.</i>

10:18.484 --> 10:20.818
OKAY, IT GOES UP.
I GET IT, I GET IT.

10:20.821 --> 10:22.487
BOSS, THERE'S GOTTA BE
ANOTHER WAY IN HERE.

10:22.488 --> 10:24.154
VENTING, CEILINGS...
THERE'S GOTTA BE ANOTHER WAY.

10:24.157 --> 10:26.958
YEAH, COPY THAT.
SPIKE, RAF?

10:26.960 --> 10:28.893
EVERYONE DOWN THERE
NEEDS TO FIND COVER.

10:28.895 --> 10:30.078
RIGHT NOW!

10:30.079 --> 10:31.262
DUE RESPECT, BUT THERE'S
NO SUCH THING AS "COVER"

10:31.264 --> 10:33.098
WITH THIS THING.

10:33.099 --> 10:34.933
<i> EVERYBODY UP TOP'S GOTTA</i>
<i> MOVE BACK RIGHT NOW.</i>

10:35.869 --> 10:37.335
ED, THAT INCLUDES YOU.

10:38.271 --> 10:40.271
EVERYONE, JUST MOVE IT BACK!

10:40.273 --> 10:42.040
CLEAR IT UP!

10:42.042 --> 10:44.743
ALL THE TRUCKS TO THE END
OF THE BLOCK, JULES.

10:44.745 --> 10:46.645
SPIKE, WHAT ABOUT YOU?

10:48.649 --> 10:49.781
I GOT A PLAN.

10:55.689 --> 10:56.354
WHAT'S THAT GUY DOING
IN THE HALL?

10:56.356 --> 10:57.672
IS THERE ANOTHER BOMB?

10:57.673 --> 10:58.989
I NEED YOU GUYS BACK
AGAINST THE WALL.

10:58.992 --> 11:00.072
THERE IS,
ISN'T THERE?

11:00.073 --> 11:01.153
RAF:
I NEED YOU GUYS
AGAINST THE WALL.

11:01.154 --> 11:02.234
NOW.
IT'S FOR YOUR SAFETY.

11:02.235 --> 11:03.315
WE NEED TO FIND A WAY OUT!

11:03.316 --> 11:04.396
RAF:
AND WE WILL. BUT RIGHT NOW,
I NEED YOU GUYS IN HERE

11:04.398 --> 11:05.397
AND AGAINST THE WALL.

11:05.399 --> 11:06.398
WOMAN:
THERE'S ANOTHER BOMB?

11:06.400 --> 11:07.866
WE'RE WORKING ON IT.

11:07.867 --> 11:09.333
HEY BUDDY, COULD I SEE YOU
FOR A SEC.

11:09.336 --> 11:10.435
YOU'RE BUILDING SECURITY,
RIGHT?

11:10.437 --> 11:11.870
YES. I-I'M...

11:11.872 --> 11:13.038
I NEED YOU
TO KEEP 'EM CALM.

11:13.040 --> 11:14.573
OKAY, CALM IS CONTAGIOUS.

11:14.574 --> 11:16.107
THE MORE TOGETHER YOU ARE, THE
BETTER THEY'LL BE, ALL RIGHT?

11:16.109 --> 11:17.909
AND IF THEIR CONDITION CHANGES,
CAN YOU JUST...

11:17.911 --> 11:19.110
YEAH, I'LL LET YOU KNOW.

11:19.112 --> 11:20.178
OKAY.

11:22.315 --> 11:24.215
(BOOTS CLOMP,
ELECTRICITY FIZZLES)

11:27.921 --> 11:29.087
RAF,
YOU GOT SOME GOOD NEWS?

11:29.089 --> 11:31.322
ED'S WORKING
ON A WAY OUT.

11:31.324 --> 11:33.191
LIQUID NITROGEN?

11:33.192 --> 11:35.059
YEAH. THE BOMB'S ARMED
ON A CLASSIC TIMER -

11:35.062 --> 11:36.861
BRITISH NUMBER-10
PENCIL FUSE.

11:36.863 --> 11:37.962
I'VE ONLY READ ABOUT THEM.

11:37.964 --> 11:40.131
WHEN OUR GUY LEFT IT,

11:40.133 --> 11:42.467
HE WOULD'VE TIGHTENED
THIS SCREW...

11:42.469 --> 11:44.936
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> IT BUSTS A GLASS VIAL,</i>
<i> RELEASING A CHEMICAL</i>

11:44.938 --> 11:48.006
<i> THAT STARTS EATING AWAY</i>
<i> AT A TINY FILAMENT.</i>

11:48.008 --> 11:49.458
<i> ONCE THAT BREAKS,</i>

11:49.459 --> 11:50.909
<i> THE FIRING PIN IS</i>
<i> RELEASED AND...</i>

11:50.911 --> 11:53.778
BOOM.
EAH,
HAT'S THE TECHNICAL TERM.

11:53.780 --> 11:57.048
IT'S BRILLIANT.
HIGH TECH BOMB,

11:57.050 --> 11:59.017
WITH AN OLD SCHOOL TIMER.

11:59.986 --> 12:02.420
TOTALLY IMMUNE TO ELECTRONIC
COUNTER-MEASURE.

12:02.422 --> 12:04.889
SO THE LIQUID NITROGEN
STOPS THE ACID?

12:04.891 --> 12:06.758
NO.
NOTHING'S GONNA STOP IT.

12:06.760 --> 12:09.994
THAT'S WHY YOU
USE THIS FUSE.

12:09.996 --> 12:13.198
IF I DO THIS RIGHT,
IT MIGHT SLOW IT DOWN.

12:13.200 --> 12:15.200
<i> RAF:</i>
<i> BUY SOME TIME.</i>

12:15.201 --> 12:17.201
YEAH, GIVE ED A CHANCE
TO GET US OUT.

12:18.972 --> 12:21.139
ANYONE'S CELL PHONE WORKING?
MINE'S BUSTED.

12:21.141 --> 12:24.109
CRAP.
MINE'S IN MY BAG.

12:24.111 --> 12:26.144
MY WIFE ALWAYS
HAS THE NEWS ON.

12:26.146 --> 12:28.113
SHE'S GOING TO SEE
ALL OF THIS.

12:28.115 --> 12:29.914
SHE'S NOT GOING TO KNOW
WHETHER I'M DEAD OR ALIVE.

12:29.916 --> 12:31.216
HEY, HEY.

12:31.217 --> 12:32.517
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
A GREAT STORY TO TELL

12:32.519 --> 12:34.369
ONCE WE GET OUT.

12:34.370 --> 12:36.220
PEOPLE WILL BUY YOU DINNER
FOR WEEKS. HUH?

12:36.223 --> 12:37.756
YEAH, IF WE GET OUT.

12:37.758 --> 12:39.290
WE'LL GET OUT.

12:40.427 --> 12:42.160
SAM:
(DAZED MOANING)

12:44.131 --> 12:45.096
SIR. ARE YOU OKAY?

12:46.032 --> 12:47.098
SAM:
YEAH.

12:48.034 --> 12:49.234
ANY CASUALTIES?

12:49.236 --> 12:52.137
UH, THERE'S TWO
LADIES HURT.

12:54.107 --> 12:56.174
(CHATTER OVER POLICE RADIO)

12:56.176 --> 12:57.876
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> SARGE? JULES.</i>

12:57.878 --> 12:59.944
SAM. WELCOME BACK.

12:59.946 --> 13:03.248
I'M GONNA GO CHECK ON HIM.

13:03.250 --> 13:05.016
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> YOU GAVE US ONE HELL</i>
<i> OF A SCARE THERE, BUDDY.</i>

13:05.018 --> 13:07.035
<i> YOU OKAY?</i>

13:07.036 --> 13:09.053
I'M SORE, BUT ALL THE PIECES
ARE IN ONE PLACE.

13:09.055 --> 13:10.455
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> BRADDOCK, YOU'RE SUPPOSED</i>
<i> TO LEAVE THE BOMBS</i>

13:10.457 --> 13:12.023
TO THE DEMOLITIONS GUYS.

13:12.025 --> 13:13.291
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> I LOVE TO.</i>

13:13.293 --> 13:14.359
RAF? HOW'S HE LOOK?

13:14.361 --> 13:16.361
HE'S GOT A HEAD WOUND,
BOSS.

13:16.363 --> 13:18.029
I'M GOOD.

13:18.031 --> 13:20.832
OKAY,
HOW 'BOUT THOSE ESCAPE
ROUTES?

13:20.834 --> 13:22.400
WE GOT NOTHING.

13:23.336 --> 13:25.236
WE'RE TRAPPED IN HERE.

13:26.306 --> 13:28.973
BOSS, WE GOT A WAY IN.
A SUBWAY VENTILATION SHAFT.

13:28.975 --> 13:30.642
<i> I'M GONNA DROP DOWN 60 FEET.</i>

13:30.643 --> 13:32.310
<i> WE'LL BE RIGHT BESIDE</i>
<i> THE BASEMENT HALL.</i>

13:32.312 --> 13:34.179
<i> WE BLAST IN,</i>
<i> DO A CAREFUL EXTRACTION.</i>

13:34.181 --> 13:35.480
LET'S GO! LET'S GO!

13:36.416 --> 13:39.250
JULES, I NEED THE HARD
ENTRY PACK, NOW!

13:39.252 --> 13:40.919
SPIKE, YOU BUY US MORE TIME?

13:40.921 --> 13:42.153
LET'S GO! LET'S GO!

13:42.155 --> 13:43.630
BACK IT UP!

13:43.631 --> 13:45.106
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> JUST DID.</i>

13:45.107 --> 13:46.582
T-I-C SAYS WE'RE AT 90 BELOW.

13:46.583 --> 13:48.058
<i>THAT SHOULD SLOW DOWN THE ACID,</i>
<i> GIVE US...</i>

13:48.061 --> 13:49.994
<i> 40 MINUTES,</i>
<i> MAYBE 45.</i>

13:49.996 --> 13:52.230
BUT IT'D SURE BE NICE
TO BE SOMEWHERE ELSE BY THEN.

13:52.232 --> 13:54.499
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> OKAY, LET'S WORK</i>
<i> WITH 40 MINUTES.</i>

13:54.501 --> 13:55.567
NOT NOW, MA.

13:58.205 --> 14:00.104
ED:
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

14:00.106 --> 14:02.140
LET'S GO, JULES.
I NEED THAT HARD ENTRY PACK.

14:02.142 --> 14:03.274
LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

14:04.211 --> 14:05.210
EXCELLENT.
THANK YOU.

14:05.212 --> 14:07.111
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> GOOD LUCK.</i>

14:07.113 --> 14:08.580
STEVE: HEY, JULES.
JULES: HEY.

14:08.582 --> 14:09.914
DISPATCH SAYS YOU HAVE
AN INJURED OFFICER

14:09.916 --> 14:11.149
WITH A WOMAN PINNED
UNDER RUBBLE.

14:11.151 --> 14:12.150
YEAH, WE'RE GONNA
GO DOWN THERE.

14:12.152 --> 14:13.084
WE'RE GONNA GET THEM OUT.

14:13.086 --> 14:15.186
THE OFFICER, IT'S SAM?

14:15.188 --> 14:17.088
JULES, GET EVERYBODY
OUTTA HERE.

14:17.090 --> 14:18.122
STEVE:
LET ME GO DOWN.

14:18.124 --> 14:19.457
IT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN,
STEVE.

14:19.459 --> 14:21.259
JULES: COME ON.
ED: ALL RIGHT.

14:21.261 --> 14:23.528
COME ON.
START YANKING THAT WOMAN
FROM UNDER THAT RUBBLE,

14:23.530 --> 14:25.363
YOU COULD KILL HER.
I NEED TO GET DOWN THERE.

14:25.365 --> 14:27.198
I CAN'T DO THAT, STEVE.
IF WE SEND YOU DOWN,

14:27.200 --> 14:29.467
YOU'RE JUST ANOTHER PERSON
WE HAVE TO BRING BACK UP.

14:29.469 --> 14:31.202
WHAT HAPPENS IF YOU CAN'T
GET HER OUT?

14:31.204 --> 14:32.403
YOU LEAVE HER CRUSHED
SHE'S DEAD IN A COUPLE OF HOURS.

14:32.405 --> 14:33.988
WE DON'T HAVE
A COUPLE HOURS.

14:33.989 --> 14:35.572
WE'RE LUCKY IF WE GET
EVERYBODY OUT AS IT IS.

14:35.575 --> 14:37.008
<i> ED:</i>
<i> BRING IT DOWN.</i>

14:37.010 --> 14:38.209
SPIKE, I'M COMING TO YOU.

14:38.211 --> 14:39.410
IF YOU WANNA HELP?
GET ON THE RADIO

14:39.412 --> 14:42.080
AND TALK US THROUGH IT.

14:46.186 --> 14:48.069
HEY, BOSS.

14:48.070 --> 14:49.953
THE BUILDING'S CLEAR.
UNIS ARE DOING ONE FINAL SWEEP.

14:49.956 --> 14:51.055
THAT'S GOOD WORK, JULES.

14:51.057 --> 14:52.390
LIST OF THE BUILDING'S
TENANTS.

14:52.392 --> 14:54.425
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> YOU LOOKING FOR A MOTIVE?</i>

14:54.427 --> 14:56.127
WITHOUT MUCH LUCK.

14:56.129 --> 14:57.562
TOO MANY COMPANIES,
TOO MANY TARGETS.

14:57.564 --> 15:00.531
LET'S TRY AND GET A READ
ON THE BOMB BUILDER.

15:00.533 --> 15:02.166
PARKER:
WE CAN TRACK HIM DOWN.

15:02.168 --> 15:03.351
GET HIM TO HELP US STOP IT.

15:03.352 --> 15:04.535
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> OKAY, SO... MOTIVE.</i>

15:04.537 --> 15:05.904
POLITICAL, FINANCIAL?

15:05.906 --> 15:08.406
TERRORISM?
A GRUDGE TO SETTLE?

15:08.408 --> 15:10.241
GIMME HALF.

15:10.243 --> 15:11.509
LET'S MAKE IT EASY FOR HIM
TO GET IN TOUCH.

15:11.511 --> 15:12.911
WINNIE.

15:12.912 --> 15:14.312
<i> WE NEED AN 800-NUMBER.</i>
<i> GET IT OUT THERE.</i>

15:14.314 --> 15:16.447
TV, RADIO, ON-LINE.

15:16.449 --> 15:17.899
LET'S GET ALL THE TIPS
TOGETHER

15:17.900 --> 15:19.350
<i> AND HAVE THEM SENT</i>
<i> DIRECTLY TO YOU.</i>

15:19.352 --> 15:20.685
I'LL FILTER THROUGH THEM
AND PATCH THROUGH ANYTHING

15:20.687 --> 15:21.686
<i> THAT LOOKS PROMISING.</i>

15:21.688 --> 15:23.288
THAT'S PERFECT.
NOW, WINNIE,

15:23.290 --> 15:24.606
I DON'T NEED TO TELL YOU-

15:24.607 --> 15:25.923
YEAH I KNOW,
MAKE IT QUICK, I KNOW.

15:25.926 --> 15:27.325
THANK YOU.

15:28.428 --> 15:30.161
(COUGHS AND MOANS)

15:30.163 --> 15:31.629
SECURITY:
HEY.

15:31.631 --> 15:32.697
HEY.

15:34.334 --> 15:35.667
HELLO?

15:35.669 --> 15:36.935
(COUGHS)

15:39.506 --> 15:41.272
WHAT HAPPENED?

15:41.274 --> 15:44.042
HEY. SHHH, SHHH, SHHH.
YOU'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

15:44.044 --> 15:45.376
THEY'RE EVACUATING
EVERYONE.

15:45.378 --> 15:48.012
RANIA:
OH MY GOD. OH MY GOD.

15:48.014 --> 15:49.180
(CRYING)
OH MY... OH MY...

15:49.182 --> 15:51.182
SECURITY:
HEY, HEY.

15:51.184 --> 15:53.351
YOUR NAME'S RANIA, RIGHT?

15:53.353 --> 15:54.686
RANIA?

15:54.688 --> 15:56.521
W-W-WHERE ARE THE OTHERS?

15:56.523 --> 15:58.589
WHERE'S DAVE? KEN?

15:59.559 --> 16:02.427
TONY:
UH... THEY'RE, THEY'RE...
THEY'RE GONNA BE FINE.

16:02.429 --> 16:05.596
THE POLICE ARE WORKING
TO GET EVERYONE OUT.

16:05.598 --> 16:06.664
RANIA.

16:07.734 --> 16:10.201
THAT'S A BEAUTIFUL NAME.

16:10.203 --> 16:12.637
IT'S LIKE RANIA, IT'S,
AH, QUEEN OF JORDAN, RIGHT?

16:12.639 --> 16:13.705
RANIA.

16:14.674 --> 16:17.275
RANIA: YEAH.
SECURITY: YEAH.

16:17.277 --> 16:19.444
YEAH.
EAH.

16:19.445 --> 16:21.612
IT'S JUST LIKE THE QUEEN.
(WHIMPERS QUIETLY)

16:24.150 --> 16:25.216
THERE.

16:28.054 --> 16:30.154
I CAN'T FEEL MY LEGS.

16:31.091 --> 16:34.359
I CAN'T,
I CAN'T FEEL MY LEGS.

16:34.361 --> 16:35.226
(CRIES)

16:41.668 --> 16:44.369
JUST LIKE I THOUGHT...
NOTHING'S GONNA BE EASY.

16:44.371 --> 16:46.571
RAF, I SHOULD BE THERE.
HOLD IT!

16:47.540 --> 16:49.474
RAF, I SHOULD BE CLOSE
RIGHT HERE.

16:49.476 --> 16:51.409
<i> RAF:</i>
<i> YOU'RE RIGHT ON THE OTHER</i>
<i> SIDE, ED.</i>

16:51.411 --> 16:53.277
PLACE THE CHARGE,
THEN WE'LL BLAST RIGHT THROUGH.

16:53.279 --> 16:54.646
NOT SO FAST.

16:54.647 --> 16:56.014
SPIKE, WE GOT NINE PEOPLE
TO PULLOUT.

16:56.015 --> 16:57.382
SPIKE:
IF YOU BLOW THROUGH NOW
THERE'S GONNA BE ANYBODY.

16:57.384 --> 16:58.783
THERE'S A MOTION SENSITIVE
SWITCH ON THIS THING.

16:58.785 --> 17:00.385
I GOTTA DEACTIVATE IT.

17:00.387 --> 17:02.065
THE BLAST COULD SET IT OFF.

17:02.066 --> 17:03.744
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SPIKE, WHY WOULD IT</i>
<i> IF THE FIRST TWO DIDN'T?</i>

17:03.745 --> 17:05.423
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> 'CAUSE THE BOMBER</i>
<i> KNEW HIS ANGLES, BOSS.</i>

17:05.425 --> 17:06.808
ED'S COMING IN WAY TOO CLOSE.

17:06.809 --> 17:08.192
SPIKE: YOU GOTTA BE CAREFUL.
PARKER: OKAY.

17:08.194 --> 17:09.260
SPIKE:
SO DON'T LET HIM
TAKE ANY CHANCES.

17:09.262 --> 17:11.062
ALL RIGHT, DEACTIVATE.
GO CAREFUL.

17:11.064 --> 17:13.297
<i> ED:</i>
<i> CHARGE IS SET.</i>
<i> PULL ME BACK UP.</i>

17:13.299 --> 17:15.199
HOW LONG, SPIKE?

17:15.201 --> 17:17.268
SECONDS AWAY. I JUST GOTTA
MAKE SURE THE PIN DOESN'T DROP

17:17.270 --> 17:18.736
IF THE BOX MOVES.

17:21.041 --> 17:24.375
<i> ED:</i>
<i> LET'S GO, GO, GO.</i>
<i> LET'S GO!</i>

17:24.377 --> 17:26.144
UP, UP, UP! ALL RIGHT,
RIGHT THERE, RIGHT THERE.

17:26.146 --> 17:27.678
LET'S GO!
DROP IT DOWN, DROP IT DOWN!

17:27.680 --> 17:28.746
UNHOOK ME.

17:30.450 --> 17:31.816
<i> RAF:</i>
<i> EVERYONE MOVE BACK</i>
<i> TO THE CORNER</i>

17:31.818 --> 17:33.317
AND KEEP YOUR HEADS DOWN NOW!

17:33.319 --> 17:35.586
TAKE COVER!
GO, GO, NOW! NOW!

17:37.190 --> 17:39.657
CHARGE IS IN PLACE,
READY TO BLOW.

17:39.659 --> 17:41.292
SPIKE...

17:41.294 --> 17:42.961
GOOD TO BLOW!

17:42.962 --> 17:44.629
LET THIS PLEASE BE THE LAST
THING WE BLOW UP TODAY.

17:44.631 --> 17:46.464
COUNTING DOWN.
FIVE...

17:46.466 --> 17:47.799
FOUR... THREE...

17:48.735 --> 17:49.801
TWO... ONE.
(REMOTE BEEPS)

17:55.408 --> 17:57.675
<i> ED:</i>
<i> COUNTING DOWN.</i>
<i> FIVE...</i>

17:57.677 --> 17:59.844
<i> FOUR... THREE...</i>

17:59.846 --> 18:01.813
TWO... ONE.
(REMOTE BEEPS)

18:01.815 --> 18:03.581
(CHARGE DETONATES)

18:12.759 --> 18:14.609
(TRUCK DOOR SHUTS)

18:14.610 --> 18:16.460
HEY, UH, SAM, IT'S STEVE.
YOU THERE?

18:16.463 --> 18:18.196
SAM:
STEVE, SHE'S TOO DEEPLY
BURIED FOR TOURNIQUETS.

18:18.198 --> 18:19.464
STEVE:
YEAH. YOU KNOW WHAT?

18:19.465 --> 18:20.731
<i> I'VE SEEN THE PICTURES</i>
<i> YOU TOOK.</i>

18:20.732 --> 18:21.998
I'M SENDING DOWN SOME MEDS.

18:21.999 --> 18:23.265
CAN YOU, UH, SET UP
AN IV DRIP?

18:23.269 --> 18:24.469
WE JUST HAVE TO KEEP
HER HYDRATED.

18:24.471 --> 18:26.087
SAM:
NO PROBLEM,
JUST GET IT DOWN HERE.

18:26.088 --> 18:27.704
<i> STEVE:</i>
<i> I'M ON IT. I'LL SEND IT DOWN</i>
<i> WITH THE AIR JACK.</i>

18:27.707 --> 18:30.341
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY,
RANIA.

18:30.343 --> 18:32.410
PLEASE, JUST GET ME OUT.

18:35.582 --> 18:37.849
THE HOLE'S GOOD.
WE'RE PUNCHED THROUGH.

18:37.850 --> 18:40.117
<i> ED:</i>
<i> THE HARNESS IS ON ITS WAY,</i>
<i> AND I'M SENDING DOWN THE MEDS.</i>

18:40.854 --> 18:42.504
ON IT'S WAY.

18:42.505 --> 18:44.155
IT'S A LONG WAY DOWN,
IT'S GONNA TAKE SOME TIME.

18:44.157 --> 18:45.123
AND NINE PEOPLE
ARE DOWN THERE.

18:45.125 --> 18:46.491
HOW MUCH TIME
FOR EACH PERSON?

18:46.493 --> 18:49.160
ED:
UP AND DOWN,
MAYBE THREE MINUTES PER PERSON.

18:49.162 --> 18:52.730
(EXHALES)
MY GOD, THAT'S 27 MINUTES.

18:52.732 --> 18:53.865
THAT'S NOT ENOUGH TIME.

18:53.867 --> 18:55.283
RAF:
IF YOU SOME TOOLS DOWN HERE,

18:55.284 --> 18:56.700
WE CAN CUT THE METAL
AND MAKE THE HOLE BIGGER.

18:56.703 --> 18:58.436
WE MIGHT BE ABLE
TO TAKE THIS BOMB RIGHT OUT.

18:58.438 --> 19:00.171
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SPIKE, THAT COULD WORK?</i>

19:00.173 --> 19:01.672
SPIKE:
COULD WORK, OR WE COULD TRIP
ANOTHER COUNTER-MEASURE

19:01.674 --> 19:03.207
AND BLOW IT UP EARLY.

19:03.209 --> 19:04.342
OKAY, BUT WE GOTTA TRY,

19:04.343 --> 19:05.476
BECAUSE NOT EVERYBODY'S
GONNA MAKE IT.

19:05.477 --> 19:06.610
YOU'RE SAYING I CAN'T
DEFUSE A BOMB?

19:06.613 --> 19:08.263
<i> ED:</i>
<i> YOU'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME.</i>

19:08.264 --> 19:09.914
LET'S GET THAT FIRST CIVILIAN
TO THE HOLE. NOW!

19:09.916 --> 19:11.449
<i> LET'S GO!</i>
<i> LET'S DO IT NOW!</i>

19:11.451 --> 19:13.351
COPY THAT, EDDIE.

19:14.287 --> 19:15.386
<i> ED:</i>
<i> RAF, HOW'S IT LOOKING?</i>

19:15.388 --> 19:17.455
ALL RIGHT, GOT THE PACKAGE.

19:17.457 --> 19:19.457
(HARNESS BUCKLES CLICK)

19:27.800 --> 19:31.903
RAF:
OKAY, I'M GETTING CLAIRE
HOOKED UP NOW.

19:31.905 --> 19:34.239
SAM: OKAY, RANIA?
RANIA: YES?

19:34.240 --> 19:36.574
SAM:
I'M GONNA PUT SOME FLUIDS
IN YOU, OKAY?

19:36.576 --> 19:38.192
YOU'VE DONE THIS BEFORE?

19:38.193 --> 19:39.809
SAM:
SURE, ARMY TRAINED,
IN THE FIELD.

19:39.812 --> 19:43.648
SOLDIERS THOUGH,
THEY'RE NOT AS TOUGH AS YOU ARE.

19:43.650 --> 19:45.200
<i> OKAY, TONY...</i>

19:45.201 --> 19:46.751
I NEED YOU FIND SOMETHING
TO HANG THIS OFF, OKAY?

19:46.753 --> 19:47.818
OKAY.

19:49.756 --> 19:52.290
RAF:
ALL RIGHT, ED, STAND BY.

19:52.292 --> 19:53.691
LITTLE MORE TENSION, ED.

19:53.693 --> 19:54.959
LITTLE MORE.

19:55.895 --> 19:57.862
LITTLE MORE.

19:57.864 --> 20:01.199
ALL RIGHT,
SHE'S COMING UP, ED.

20:03.836 --> 20:06.270
SAM: (HUSHED TONE)
STEVE, SHE'S SHAKING
PRETTY BADLY.

20:06.272 --> 20:07.583
<i> STEVE:</i>
<i> IT'S SHOCK.</i>

20:07.584 --> 20:08.895
HER ORGANS COULD BE
SHUTTING DOWN.

20:08.896 --> 20:10.207
WE NEED TO START HER
ON THAT ON THAT IV.

20:10.210 --> 20:11.275
ON IT.

20:15.848 --> 20:18.616
ALL RIGHT,
CLAIRE'S ON HER WAY.

20:18.618 --> 20:19.850
ALL RIGHT, WHO'S DAVE?
YOU'RE NEXT.

20:19.852 --> 20:21.352
KEN:
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
WHAT?

20:21.354 --> 20:22.520
IT'S ALPHABETICAL.

20:22.522 --> 20:24.011
IT'S RANDOM
AND IT'S FAIR.

20:24.012 --> 20:25.501
<i> KEN:</i>
<i> NO, CLAIRE WAS HURT -</i>
<i> I GET THAT.</i>

20:25.502 --> 20:26.991
BUT NOW ALPHABETICAL?
HOW IS THAT FAIR?

20:26.993 --> 20:28.459
<i> I GOT A TWO YEAR-OLD</i>
<i> DAUGHTER,</i>

20:28.460 --> 20:29.926
YOU THINK IT'S FAIR THAT
HER DAD DIES DOWN HERE?

20:29.929 --> 20:31.179
WE'RE ALL GONNA
GET OUTTA HERE, KEN.

20:31.180 --> 20:32.430
YEAH, EASY FOR YOU TO SAY,
ANDERSON.

20:32.432 --> 20:33.276
HEY!

20:33.277 --> 20:34.121
HEY, HEY, HEY,
CAN YOU GUARANTEE

20:34.122 --> 20:34.966
THAT ALL OF US
GET OUT OF HERE?

20:34.968 --> 20:36.968
NO. YOU CAN'T.

20:36.970 --> 20:38.469
LOOK, I AM LAST.

20:38.471 --> 20:39.904
PLEASE, DAVE,
FOR THE LOVE OF-

20:39.906 --> 20:40.972
KEN, IT'S MY TURN.

20:40.974 --> 20:42.640
IR!
HEY-HEY, BUDDY,
SETTLE DOWN.

20:42.642 --> 20:44.175
GET YOUR HANDS OFF OF ME!

20:44.176 --> 20:45.709
<i> WHY DO YOU DECIDE WHO LIVES</i>
<i> AND WHO DIES?</i>

20:45.712 --> 20:48.246
HEY! EVERY MINUTE YOU SPEND
FIGHTING ME

20:48.248 --> 20:50.014
IS A MINUTE I SHOULD BE WORKING
TO GET YOU OUTTA HERE.

20:50.016 --> 20:52.883
<i> TONY:</i>
<i> YOU CAN TAKE MY PLACE.</i>

20:52.885 --> 20:54.252
REALLY?

20:54.254 --> 20:56.454
TONY KRAMKOV.
TAKE IT. I'LL GO LAST.

20:56.456 --> 20:59.423
(RELIEVED BREATHS)
THANK YOU.

20:59.425 --> 21:00.491
OKAY.

21:04.397 --> 21:06.831
US GUYS IN UNIFORM,
WE STICK TOGETHER.

21:06.833 --> 21:08.766
YOU'RE A GOOD MAN, TONY.

21:08.768 --> 21:10.301
ED:
WE'RE GOOD.

21:11.037 --> 21:12.003
(DRILL WHIRS)

21:12.005 --> 21:14.405
CRACKING THE SHELL NOW.

21:18.311 --> 21:19.343
BOSS...

21:19.345 --> 21:21.646
<i> WE GOT MORE TROUBLE.</i>

21:21.648 --> 21:22.913
TALK TO ME, SPIKE.

21:22.915 --> 21:24.749
THE GUY WHO BUILT THIS THING

21:24.751 --> 21:26.784
DID NOT WANT ANYONE
TO GET HIS HANDS ON IT.

21:26.786 --> 21:28.386
<i> SENDING YOU A VIDEO RIGHT NOW.</i>

21:28.388 --> 21:31.322
THAT PYREX IS PROTECTED
BY INFRA-RED.

21:31.324 --> 21:33.658
I CRACK THE GLASS,
IT DETONATES.

21:33.660 --> 21:34.776
HOW'S THAT?

21:34.777 --> 21:35.893
THE I-R IS A TRIP WIRE.

21:35.895 --> 21:38.329
I BREAK THE GLASS,
I BREAKS THE BEAM,

21:38.331 --> 21:39.764
IT TRIGGERS IMMEDIATELY.

21:39.766 --> 21:41.900
WHAT ABOUT THE KEYPAD?

21:41.901 --> 21:44.035
YEAH, IT PROBABLY SHUTS OFF
THE INFRA-RED

21:44.037 --> 21:46.704
THEN MAYBE I CAN CRACK THE GLASS
AND GET TO THAT FUSE, BUT...

21:46.706 --> 21:48.589
BUT WHAT?

21:48.590 --> 21:50.473
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> BUT THIS THING'S A FORTRESS,</i>
<i> BOSS.</i>

21:50.476 --> 21:52.610
I MEAN, I PUT IN THE WRONG
CODE...

21:52.612 --> 21:54.478
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH...

21:55.848 --> 21:58.849
I'M NOT GONNA LET THAT HAPPEN.

21:58.851 --> 22:01.319
SARGE, GUY ON THE 800 NUMBER
SAYS HE'S THE BOMBER.

22:01.321 --> 22:03.587
EDDIE,
JACK'S ON THE WAY.

22:03.589 --> 22:05.323
WINNIE, PATCH HIM THROUGH.

22:07.393 --> 22:10.328
<i> ED:</i>
<i> IT'S OKAY. WE GOT YOU,</i>
<i> LET'S GO.</i>

22:11.397 --> 22:12.963
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
GOOD MAN, GOOD MAN.

22:12.965 --> 22:15.333
LET'S GET HIM UP,
LET'S GET HIM UP.

22:21.341 --> 22:22.873
<i> BOMBER:</i>
<i> THE BOMB IS THE MESSAGE</i>

22:22.875 --> 22:24.909
<i> AND THIS MESSAGE</i>
<i> IS FOR THE PIG BANKERS</i>

22:24.911 --> 22:27.645
<i> GETTING FAT OFF THE CORPSES</i>
<i> OF THE POOR.</i>

22:27.647 --> 22:29.380
HELLO, THIS IS SERGEANT
GREG PARKER

22:29.382 --> 22:31.549
WITH THE POLICE STRATEGIC
RESPONSE UNIT.

22:31.551 --> 22:34.919
AH, THE POLICE.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME AGAIN?

22:34.921 --> 22:36.354
IT'S GREG PARKER, SIR.

22:36.356 --> 22:38.072
<i> BOMBER:</i>
<i> GREG PARKER,</i>

22:38.073 --> 22:39.789
<i> YOUR HANDS ARE BEING HELD</i>
<i> BY THE GOVERNMENT ON ONE SIDE</i>

22:39.792 --> 22:42.760
<i> AND BY THE BANKS</i>
<i> ON THE OTHER...</i>

22:42.762 --> 22:45.129
(WHISPERING)
OKAY, BOSS, THERE'S A BANK
ON FLOORS EIGHT THROUGH 12,

22:45.131 --> 22:46.506
<i> AND ALSO AN AEROSPACE</i>
<i> COMPANY,</i>

22:46.507 --> 22:47.882
<i> I'M GONNA FIND SOMEBODY</i>
<i> TO TALK TO.</i>

22:47.883 --> 22:49.258
<i> ED:</i>
<i> WINNIE, SOUNDS LIKE</i>
<i> IT COULD BE OUR GUY.</i>

22:49.259 --> 22:50.634
RUN A TRACE,
SEND SOME CRUISERS.

22:50.636 --> 22:51.635
<i> DO IT NOW.</i>

22:51.637 --> 22:53.137
COPY THAT.

22:53.138 --> 22:54.638
WORK HIM, BOSS.
SIGNIFICANT DATES,

22:54.639 --> 22:56.139
FAVOURITE NUMBERS,
I'LL TAKE ANYTHING YOU CAN GET.

22:56.142 --> 22:58.776
SIR, I WANNA THANK YOU
FOR CALLING US TODAY.

22:58.778 --> 23:00.077
<i> BOMBER:</i>
<i> I'VE GOT YOUR ATTENTION.</i>

23:00.079 --> 23:02.780
OH, YES, SIR.
VERY MUCH SO.

23:02.782 --> 23:04.448
GOOD.

23:04.450 --> 23:05.917
TODAY THE WORLD HEARS ME.

23:05.918 --> 23:07.385
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> IS THERE A REASON</i>
<i> YOU PICKED TODAY, SIR?</i>

23:07.387 --> 23:09.453
IS THIS DATE PART
OF YOUR MESSAGE?

23:09.455 --> 23:12.089
<i> BOMBER:</i>
<i> NO, TODAY'S JUST THE START,</i>
<i> SERGEANT PARKER.</i>

23:12.091 --> 23:14.625
THERE'S GONNA BE A WHOLE
LOT MORE, JUST LIKE THIS.

23:14.627 --> 23:15.860
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> RED FLAG, BOSS.</i>

23:15.862 --> 23:16.928
A BOMB THIS COMPLEX...

23:16.929 --> 23:17.995
YOU DON'T KNOCK OFF
A BUNCH OF THEM.

23:17.997 --> 23:19.463
<i> THIS IS A ONCE IN A LIFETIME.</i>

23:19.465 --> 23:21.499
LET'S BE REAL SURE
WITH THIS, SPIKE.

23:21.501 --> 23:23.167
ASK HIM HOW HE GOT
SO MUCH DYNAMITE?

23:23.169 --> 23:25.319
SIR,

23:25.320 --> 23:27.470
CAN YOU TELL ME HOW YOU GOT
YOUR HANDS ON SO MUCH DYNAMITE?

23:27.473 --> 23:29.440
THAT'S QUITE A COUP.

23:29.441 --> 23:31.408
<i> BOMBER:</i>
<i> DON'T UNDERESTIMATE</i>
<i> THE LITTLE GUY.</i>

23:31.411 --> 23:33.177
THERE'S A LOT MORE DYNAMITE
WHERE THAT CAME FROM.

23:33.179 --> 23:34.478
AGH! WRONG ANSWER.

23:35.415 --> 23:36.947
BOMBER USED PLASTIQUE.

23:36.949 --> 23:38.883
WINNIE:
SARGE, THERE'S UNIFORMS
ARE AT THE GUY'S HOUSE.

23:38.885 --> 23:41.152
WINNIE, SEND 'EM IN.
TAKE THIS GOOFBALL DOWN.

23:41.154 --> 23:42.453
SPIKE...

23:42.455 --> 23:44.355
...WHAT YOU'RE GONNA DO
DO YOU HEAR ME?

23:44.356 --> 23:46.256
<i> (KNOCK AT THE DOOR)</i>
<i> OFFICER: POLICE OPEN UP!</i>

23:46.257 --> 23:48.157
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> LOUD AND CLEAR YOU IDIOT.</i>

23:49.095 --> 23:50.645
SPIKE...

23:50.646 --> 23:52.196
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> I KNOW, I KNOW.</i>
<i> BACK TO SQUARE ONE.</i>

23:52.198 --> 23:55.466
WE GOT 20 MINUTES
BEFORE THIS THING GOES UP.

23:55.468 --> 23:56.700
(KNOCKING)

24:00.072 --> 24:01.105
OFFICE CALLAGHAN?

24:01.107 --> 24:02.506
JULES: LUCAS BRAFT?
BRAFT: YES.

24:02.508 --> 24:03.841
APPRECIATE YOUR TIME.

24:03.842 --> 24:05.175
MY ASSISTANT SAID
YOU WANTED TO TALK TO ME.

24:05.178 --> 24:06.311
WHAT CAN I DO?

24:06.312 --> 24:07.445
WELL, I'M HOPING THAT YOU
CAN HELP US FIGURE OUT

24:07.447 --> 24:09.079
WHAT IS GOING ON HERE.

24:09.081 --> 24:10.765
YOUR COMPANY, LEWELLEN,

24:10.766 --> 24:12.450
IT OCCUPIES THE BOTTOM SEVEN
FLOORS OF THIS BUILDING.

24:12.452 --> 24:15.453
IS IT POSSIBLE THAT SOMEBODY
MIGHT BE TARGETING YOU?

24:15.455 --> 24:16.821
YES, WELL,
I SUPPOSE IT'S POSSIBLE,

24:16.823 --> 24:19.523
BUT SECURITY'S PRETTY TIGHT
AROUND OUR OFFICES.

24:19.525 --> 24:21.492
OKAY. SO MAYBE THEY'RE
ATTACKING THE BUILDING

24:21.494 --> 24:22.643
TO GET TO YOU.

24:22.644 --> 24:23.793
YES, WELL, WE'VE HAD OUR SHARE
OF THREATS.

24:23.796 --> 24:25.196
BUT MAKING MISSILE
GUIDANCE SYSTEMS

24:25.198 --> 24:27.031
MAKES US A VILLAIN
TO SOME PEOPLE.

24:27.033 --> 24:28.966
ANTI-WAR TYPES?

24:28.967 --> 24:30.900
SOMETIMES...
NOT EXCLUSIVELY.

24:30.903 --> 24:33.504
THIS DEVICE IS HIGHLY
SOPHISTICATED.

24:33.506 --> 24:35.706
CAN YOU THINK OF ANYBODY THAT
MIGHT BE HOLDING A GRUDGE?

24:40.079 --> 24:41.846
THERE'S A MAN NAMED
KANISKY.

24:41.848 --> 24:43.180
THE JACK'S COMING DOWN.

24:43.182 --> 24:44.982
ERIC, LET'S GO.

24:46.486 --> 24:47.568
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

24:47.569 --> 24:48.651
<i> RANIA:</i>
<i> SURE I AM.</i>

24:48.654 --> 24:50.554
YOU WANNA DANCE?

24:50.556 --> 24:52.256
SENSE OF HUMOR.
THAT'S A GOOD SIGN.

24:52.258 --> 24:56.660
<i> I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.</i>
<i> TONY'LL BE WITH YOU.</i>

24:56.662 --> 24:58.496
(CRIES)

24:59.232 --> 25:01.265
HE'S NOT TELLING ME
EVERYTHING.

25:01.267 --> 25:02.933
WHAT MAKES YOU SAY THAT?

25:02.935 --> 25:05.035
THE REASSURING SMILES.

25:05.037 --> 25:06.971
NO.
HE KNOWS WHAT HE'S DOING.

25:07.907 --> 25:10.975
AND THEN WHAT?
WHAT ABOUT MY LEGS?

25:10.977 --> 25:12.977
DOCTORS ARE MINUTES AWAY.

25:16.048 --> 25:18.015
IT'S TONY, RIGHT?

25:18.017 --> 25:19.083
YES.

25:22.021 --> 25:24.822
I'M GOING TO DIE,
AREN'T I?

25:30.263 --> 25:31.929
I DON'T KNOW.

25:36.068 --> 25:37.134
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> BOSS.</i>

25:37.136 --> 25:39.036
I THINK I GOT A LEAD
ON OUR BOMBER.

25:39.038 --> 25:40.604
HIS ALEXI KANISKY.

25:42.742 --> 25:45.609
BRILLIANT, ANGRY
AND FIRED.

25:45.611 --> 25:48.646
HE WORKED AT LEWELLEN
INTERNATIONAL FOR THREE YEARS -

25:48.648 --> 25:49.880
THEY MAKE MISSILE
GUIDANCE SYSTEMS.

25:49.882 --> 25:52.883
OKAY, HERE'S HIS PERSONNEL
PROFILE.

25:53.819 --> 25:56.554
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> HE WAS FIRED FOR SELLING</i>
<i> THEIR TECH TO ANOTHER FIRM.</i>

25:56.556 --> 25:58.122
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> YEAH, HE WAS WORKING</i>
<i> ON NEW PRODUCTS.</i>

25:58.124 --> 25:59.223
<i> HEAVILY HANDS-ON.</i>

25:59.225 --> 26:00.598
THAT SOUNDS LIKE A FIT.

26:00.599 --> 26:01.972
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> JULES, WHAT DO YOU THINK?</i>

26:01.973 --> 26:03.346
GUY LIKE THIS STICK AROUND
AND WATCH THE SHOW?

26:03.347 --> 26:04.720
OH, I THINK
HE'D WANNA WATCH

26:04.721 --> 26:06.094
THE COMPANY THAT SCREWED
HIM OVER COME DOWN.

26:06.098 --> 26:07.965
<i> ED:</i>
<i> LET'S GET A PICTURE</i>
<i> OUT TO THE UNIFORMS.</i>

26:07.967 --> 26:10.234
HAVE EVERYONE START
LOOKING.

26:10.236 --> 26:13.804
OKAY, I'M GONNA GO TO HIS HOUSE
AND SEE WHAT I CAN FIND.

26:16.309 --> 26:18.342
HEY, SPIKE. HOW YOU DOING
DOWN THERE, BUDDY?

26:18.344 --> 26:21.779
<i> OKAY, NUMBERS TOUCHED</i>
<i> ARE, UH, TWO, FOUR,</i>

26:21.781 --> 26:23.614
<i> FIVE AND SIX.</i>

26:23.616 --> 26:25.716
<i> TWO AND FOUR LOOK LIKE</i>
<i> THEY WERE DOUBLE TOUCHED.</i>

26:25.718 --> 26:28.185
SO THAT NARROWS DOWN
OUR POSSIBLE CODE COMBINATIONS.

26:28.187 --> 26:29.853
FROM INFINITY TO...

26:30.957 --> 26:32.356
ABOUT HALF THAT.

26:34.226 --> 26:35.859
RAF:
UP, UP, UP. ALL RIGHT.

26:35.861 --> 26:37.628
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

26:38.831 --> 26:39.897
(RINGING)

26:40.833 --> 26:42.700
MA, YOU CAN'T CALL-

26:43.669 --> 26:45.703
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

26:45.705 --> 26:47.605
A CLOT?

26:47.607 --> 26:49.106
NO, HE'S SUPPOSED TO GO
HOME TODAY.

26:49.108 --> 26:50.174
(EXHALES)

26:51.110 --> 26:52.376
SPIKE?

26:52.378 --> 26:53.811
MA. I CAN'T...

26:55.114 --> 26:56.714
YEAH.

26:56.716 --> 26:58.048
YEAH.

26:58.050 --> 27:00.250
<i> OKAY.</i>
<i> AS SOON AS I CAN.</i>

27:01.187 --> 27:02.353
WHAT'S UP, BRO?

27:02.355 --> 27:04.322
MY DAD. THEY'RE SAYING

27:04.323 --> 27:06.290
HE'S PROBABLY NOT GONNA
MAKE IT THROUGH THE NIGHT.

27:07.927 --> 27:09.393
RAF:
WE CLEAR THE CIVILIANS;
YOU'RE FIRST UP.

27:09.395 --> 27:10.917
NO.

27:10.918 --> 27:12.440
RAF:
SPIKE, YOU GOTTA GO.

27:12.441 --> 27:13.963
NO. IT'S MY CALL.
THIS IS THE DRILL, OKAY?

27:13.966 --> 27:15.866
I'M LAST MAN OUT.

27:15.868 --> 27:17.368
RAF:
OKAY, PEOPLE,
WE GOTTA MOVE.

27:17.370 --> 27:19.770
YOU GOTTA KNOW WHERE
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE.

27:19.772 --> 27:21.639
<i> BOSS, FIND KANISKY.</i>
<i> OKAY?</i>

27:21.641 --> 27:22.640
<i> I CAN CRACK THIS THING.</i>

27:22.642 --> 27:24.842
YOU BET, BUDDY.
WE'RE ON IT.

27:25.778 --> 27:27.578
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> GUYS, CHECK YOUR PHONES.</i>

27:27.579 --> 27:29.379
<i> I JUST SENT A PICTURE</i>
<i> OF OUR SUBJECT, ALEX KANISKY.</i>

27:29.382 --> 27:33.417
BOSS. I THINK YOU CAN
CALL OFF THAT SEARCH.

27:33.419 --> 27:35.152
SAM, CHECK YOUR PDA.

27:39.258 --> 27:40.324
(PDA CHIMES)

27:48.200 --> 27:50.334
THE BOMBER'S BEEN DOWN HERE
WITH US THIS WHOLE TIME.

27:54.940 --> 27:56.940
WE GOT THE GUY WHO MADE
THE BOMB RIGHT HERE, LET'S JUST-

27:56.942 --> 27:58.375
'KAY, WE CAN'T CONFRONT HIM.

27:58.376 --> 27:59.809
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> BUT WE NEED HIM...</i>
<i> I NEED HIM.</i>

27:59.810 --> 28:01.243
<i> ED:</i>
<i> GO, GO, WE'RE RUNNING</i>
<i> OUT OF TIME.</i>

28:01.247 --> 28:02.946
LET'S GO! LET'S MOVE!

28:02.948 --> 28:04.715
LET'S CONVINCE HIM
TO DEFUSE THE BOMB OFF.

28:04.717 --> 28:06.016
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> WHAT IF HE HAS A DETONATOR?</i>

28:06.018 --> 28:07.284
THEN JUST BLOWS IT UP EARLY.

28:07.286 --> 28:08.886
SO WE CONVINCE HIM
AT GUNPOINT.

28:08.888 --> 28:10.388
BOSS IS RIGHT.
YOU CAN'T RISK THAT.

28:10.389 --> 28:11.889
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> 12 MINUTES</i>
<i> BEFORE THE BOMB GOES OFF.</i>

28:11.891 --> 28:13.090
WE'VE GOT TWO MORE
CIVILIANS?

28:13.092 --> 28:15.092
YEAH.
INCLUDING RANIA.

28:15.094 --> 28:16.277
AND WE'RE ALMOST READY
WITH THE GEAR.

28:16.278 --> 28:17.461
<i> WE JUST GOTTA JACK UP</i>
<i> THE RUBBLE.</i>

28:17.463 --> 28:19.897
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> LET'S DO IT.</i>

28:21.967 --> 28:23.033
<i> KEN:</i>
<i> IT'S HERE.</i>

28:24.704 --> 28:25.836
<i> SAM: TONY.</i>
<i> TONY: YES?</i>

28:25.838 --> 28:27.371
SAM: I NEED YOUR HELP.
TONY: OKAY.

28:27.373 --> 28:29.707
SAM:
WE'RE GONNA JACK THIS UP,
OKAY?

28:29.709 --> 28:31.909
<i> WHEN IT STARTS RISING</i>
<i> I NEED YOU TO FIND ROCK,</i>

28:31.911 --> 28:33.561
<i> CONCRETE, ANYTHING.</i>

28:33.562 --> 28:35.212
JAM IT IN,
AND MAKE SURE IT DOESN'T FALL.

28:35.214 --> 28:37.014
WHY IS THIS GUY HELPING US?

28:37.016 --> 28:38.382
ON THE SAME DAY HE TRIES
TO PULL DOWN A BUILDING

28:38.384 --> 28:40.084
FULL OF PEOPLE?

28:40.085 --> 28:41.785
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> I THINK HE WANTED TO DESTROY</i>
<i> THE BUILDING,</i>

28:41.786 --> 28:43.486
I DON'T THINK HE WANTED
TO HURT ANYBODY.

28:43.487 --> 28:45.187
<i> THOSE TWO BOMBS WERE SET</i>
<i> 10 MINUTES BEFORE THIS ONE.</i>

28:45.191 --> 28:46.890
HE WANTED PEOPLE TO GET
OUT OF THE BUILDING.

28:46.892 --> 28:48.192
THEN HE WAS TRYING TO GET
PEOPLE OUT OF THE SERVER ROOM,

28:48.194 --> 28:49.660
NOW HE'S HELPING US.

28:49.661 --> 28:51.127
PARKER:
OKAY, SPIKE,
JULES IS AT HIS HOUSE.

28:51.130 --> 28:53.030
WINNIE'S DUG UP
AN OLD CO-WORKER.

28:53.032 --> 28:55.299
ALL RIGHT? LET'S...
LET'S TRY TO UNLOCK THIS GUY.

28:55.301 --> 28:57.935
BUT WE DO NOT TIP OUR
HAND UNTIL RANIA'S OUT.

28:57.937 --> 28:59.002
GOT IT.

29:01.073 --> 29:02.940
EDDIE.

29:02.942 --> 29:04.775
<i> ANYWAY WE GET OUR PEOPLE</i>
<i> OUTTA THERE QUICKER?</i>

29:04.777 --> 29:07.444
TOP SPEED'S STILL
THREE MINUTES EACH.

29:07.446 --> 29:11.448
THREE MINUTES TIMES FIVE
PEOPLE WE HAVE LEFT...

29:11.450 --> 29:13.434
(SIGHS) EDDIE...

29:13.435 --> 29:15.419
<i> SO WE'RE FIVE MINUTES</i>
<i> AND TWO TO THREE PEOPLE SHORT.</i>

29:15.421 --> 29:17.855
MAYBE SPIKE'S MATH IS OFF.

29:19.458 --> 29:20.524
(SIGHS)

29:25.297 --> 29:27.331
LOOKS LIKE HE WAS
EXPECTING US, SARGE.

29:27.333 --> 29:28.499
WHAT DO YOU SEE, JULES?

29:28.501 --> 29:30.000
<i> WELL, THE DOOR WAS OPEN.</i>

29:30.002 --> 29:32.035
AND THEN THESE FILES
NEATLY STACKED.

29:32.037 --> 29:33.437
RIGHT ON THE KITCHEN
COUNTER.

29:33.439 --> 29:34.404
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> OKAY, FAST AS YOU CAN.</i>

29:34.406 --> 29:35.405
ANYTHING YOU CAN FIND.

29:35.407 --> 29:37.007
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> COPY THAT.</i>

29:37.009 --> 29:39.209
BARB LEWIS?
COME ON IN.

29:40.146 --> 29:41.562
PROMISE I WON'T
KEEP YOU LONG.

29:41.563 --> 29:42.979
I WAS JUST HOPING
YOU CAN TELL ME SOMETHING

29:42.982 --> 29:45.149
ABOUT ALEXI KANISKY.

29:45.151 --> 29:47.218
IS HE INVOLVED
IN THESE BOMBINGS?

29:47.219 --> 29:49.286
WELL,
WE'RE TO FIGURE THAT OUT.

30:01.233 --> 30:03.500
I CAN'T IMAGINE HE HAS
ANYTHING TO DO WITH THIS.

30:03.502 --> 30:05.068
I WORKED WITH HIM
FOR YEARS.

30:05.070 --> 30:07.070
UNTIL HE WAS FIRED?

30:07.072 --> 30:09.406
CAME OUT OF THE BLUE.

30:10.376 --> 30:11.776
ALEXI:
HEY, HEY.

30:11.777 --> 30:13.177
BRAFT:
WE'LL BE FILING CHARGES
WITH THE POLICE.

30:13.179 --> 30:14.344
I'M DEEPLY DISAPPOINTED.

30:14.346 --> 30:16.146
LOOK, I HAVE DONE
NOTHING WRONG.

30:16.148 --> 30:19.049
I GAVE YOU EVERYTHING,
MY WORK, MY TIME, MY IDEAS.

30:19.051 --> 30:20.150
I TOOK YOU
INTO THIS COMPANY.

30:20.152 --> 30:21.819
I GAVE YOU THE BEST
OPPORTUNITIES.

30:21.821 --> 30:23.699
I STOOD BY YOU.

30:23.700 --> 30:25.578
WOULD YOUR LOYALTY
HAVE BEEN SO MUCH TO ASK?

30:25.579 --> 30:27.457
YOU HAVE MY LOYALTY,
SINCE THE FIRST DAY.

30:27.459 --> 30:29.860
<i> I GAVE YOU EVERYTHING!</i>

30:30.596 --> 30:32.830
I ONLY WISH THAT WERE TRUE.

30:32.832 --> 30:35.065
<i> ALEXI:</i>
<i> OKAY, OKAY...</i>

30:37.837 --> 30:41.104
<i> BARB:</i>
<i> HE WAS ESCORTED</i>
<i> FROM THE BUILDING.</i>

30:41.106 --> 30:42.239
SOME OF LEWELLEN'S
TECHNOLOGY

30:42.241 --> 30:44.241
WAS BEING LEAKED
TO A COMPETITOR.

30:44.243 --> 30:46.076
IT WAS ALL TRACED BACK
TO ALEXI.

30:46.078 --> 30:48.178
WHY DID HE DO IT?

30:48.180 --> 30:49.479
FRUSTRATION?

30:49.481 --> 30:51.415
HIS PROJECT - GALINA -

30:51.417 --> 30:53.183
<i> NEVER WORKED</i>
<i> DURING FIELD TESTS.</i>

30:53.185 --> 30:55.452
THE PRESSURE
WAS PRETTY INTENSE.

30:55.454 --> 30:57.988
MAYBE HE WAS TRYING
TO GET BACK AT THE COMPANY

30:57.990 --> 30:59.156
FOR NOT SUPPORTING HIM?

30:59.158 --> 31:01.458
YOU NEVER ASKED HIM?

31:01.460 --> 31:04.094
I CALLED HIM A FEW TIMES
AFTER HE WAS FIRED...

31:04.096 --> 31:05.229
HE NEVER CALLED ME BACK.

31:07.233 --> 31:09.466
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> THANK YOU, MS. LEWIS,</i>
<i> FOR COMING IN.</i>

31:09.468 --> 31:11.602
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> OKAY, SARGE, I THINK I HAVE</i>
<i> A HANDLE ON THIS.</i>

31:11.604 --> 31:13.537
HE WAS OBSESSED
WITH A PROJECT CALLED-

31:13.539 --> 31:14.872
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> GALINA.</i>

31:14.874 --> 31:16.106
EXACTLY.

31:16.108 --> 31:17.274
<i> BUT HE COULDN'T</i>
<i> GET IT TO WORK.</i>

31:17.276 --> 31:18.859
<i> SOME NEW TECHNOLOGY,</i>

31:18.860 --> 31:20.443
BUT THERE'S PAGE AFTER PAGE
FROM DIFFERENT DEPARTMENTS

31:20.446 --> 31:22.346
<i> IN THE COMPANY,</i>

31:22.347 --> 31:24.247
AND EVERY PIECE OF THE GUIDANCE
SYSTEM WORKED.

31:24.250 --> 31:25.515
BUT IT ALWAYS FAILED
IN THE FIELD.

31:25.517 --> 31:26.900
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> THAT'S WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE</i>

31:26.901 --> 31:28.284
EVEN THOUGH THE PARTS
ALL TESTED OUT.

31:28.287 --> 31:30.087
WHAT, SO HE SELLS
COMPANY SECRETS?

31:30.089 --> 31:31.288
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> AND WHEN HE'S CAUGHT</i>
<i> HE GOES ROGUE</i>

31:31.290 --> 31:33.056
AND PLANTS A BOMB?

31:33.058 --> 31:34.358
DOESN'T FEEL RIGHT.

31:34.360 --> 31:35.893
NO.

31:35.895 --> 31:37.394
ESPECIALLY IF HE'S DOWN
THERE TRYING TO HELP.

31:37.396 --> 31:38.295
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> THERE' S SOMETHING, JULES.</i>

31:38.297 --> 31:40.197
JUST KEEP DIGGING.

31:40.199 --> 31:41.198
<i> SPIKE?</i>

31:41.200 --> 31:42.432
I HEARD IT ALL, BOSS.

31:42.434 --> 31:44.434
SAM:
OKAY, WE'RE READY.

31:45.571 --> 31:46.970
<i> RANIA:</i>
<i> IT HURTS.</i>
<i> (PAINED WHIMPER)</i>

31:46.972 --> 31:48.338
SAM:
ALMOST THERE.

31:49.308 --> 31:51.208
(PAINED YELP)
IT HURTS.

31:51.210 --> 31:53.277
ALMOST THERE.

31:53.279 --> 31:55.412
OKAY. SPIKE,
GRAB THE IV PLEASE.

31:55.414 --> 31:57.347
RAF, ON THREE.

31:58.350 --> 31:59.650
ONE, TWO, THREE!

32:00.586 --> 32:02.686
RANIA:
(PAINED CRIES)

32:02.688 --> 32:04.087
SHE'S CLEAR.

32:04.089 --> 32:05.155
NICE.

32:05.157 --> 32:06.323
<i> RANIA:</i>
<i> (WHIMPERING)</i>

32:06.325 --> 32:07.557
HOW YOU DOING?

32:10.296 --> 32:11.428
<i> STEVE:</i>
<i> NOW THE MOST IMPORTANT</i>
<i> THING,</i>

32:11.430 --> 32:14.097
GET A TOURNIQUET ON EACH LEG.

32:17.169 --> 32:18.402
WELL, SHE'S NOT BLEEDING.

32:18.404 --> 32:20.070
IT'S NOT BLOOD LOSS -

32:20.072 --> 32:21.338
IT'S WHAT HER BODY
WAS PRODUCING

32:21.340 --> 32:23.173
WHEN IT WAS BEING
CRUSHED.

32:23.175 --> 32:25.208
<i> PHOSPHOROUS. POTASSIUM.</i>

32:25.210 --> 32:26.276
IF THEY GET INTO
HER CIRCULATION

32:26.278 --> 32:28.045
HER KIDNEYS COULD FAIL.

32:28.047 --> 32:29.680
YOU HANGING IN THERE?

32:29.682 --> 32:31.715
YES.
THANK YOU.

32:31.717 --> 32:32.983
THANK YOU.

32:34.253 --> 32:35.552
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> ALL RIGHT.</i>

32:36.488 --> 32:37.554
READY?

32:37.556 --> 32:39.489
SHOULD BE OKAY.

32:39.491 --> 32:40.691
OKAY...

32:41.627 --> 32:43.493
ONE, TWO THREE.

32:43.495 --> 32:45.295
RANIA:
(PAINED CRIES)

32:56.575 --> 33:00.243
(RANIA BREATHES SHAKILY,
HARNESS BUCKLES CLANK)

33:00.245 --> 33:01.611
SO YOU'RE NEXT.
OKAY?

33:01.613 --> 33:05.382
A COUPLE OF MINUTES
AND YOU'LL BE OUT OF HERE.

33:05.384 --> 33:07.251
NONE OF THIS SHOULD
HAVE HAPPENED.

33:07.252 --> 33:09.119
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> I COULDN'T AGREE MORE.</i>

33:09.120 --> 33:10.987
I'D LIKE TO THANK YOU
FOR ALL THE HELP TODAY.

33:10.990 --> 33:12.489
YOU THREE SHOULD GO UP NEXT.

33:12.491 --> 33:14.257
I-I HAVE NO FAMILY.
I'LL GO LAST.

33:14.259 --> 33:16.093
NO, I CAN'T LET THAT HAPPEN.
WE'VE GOT RULES -

33:16.095 --> 33:17.227
ABOUT PROTECTING LIFE.

33:17.229 --> 33:19.496
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> OKAY, LET'S GO.</i>

33:19.498 --> 33:21.565
RANIA:
(PAINED WHIMPERS)

33:24.770 --> 33:26.503
HEY... SAM.

33:26.505 --> 33:27.738
YEAH?

33:27.740 --> 33:31.475
<i> RANIA:</i>
<i> THANK YOU FOR GETTING ME</i>
<i> THIS FAR.</i>

33:31.477 --> 33:33.377
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.

33:33.379 --> 33:35.245
'KAY,
GIVE US A LITTLE SLACK.

33:35.247 --> 33:36.246
'KAY.

33:36.248 --> 33:38.482
GO, GO.
RANIA? RANIA?

33:39.752 --> 33:42.352
<i> 'KAY, GET HER UP, ED.</i>
<i> GO, GO, GO!</i>

33:42.354 --> 33:43.720
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> NO MATTER HOW LONG</i>
<i> I'M A POLICE OFFICER...</i>

33:43.722 --> 33:47.290
CALLS LIKE THIS,
IT'S ALWAYS HARD.

33:47.292 --> 33:49.593
<i>THING IS, I DON'T THINK ANYBODY</i>
<i>WAS SUPPOSED TO GET HURT TODAY.</i>

33:49.595 --> 33:51.328
<i> WHAT DO YOU THINK?</i>

33:51.330 --> 33:52.746
I DON'T KNOW.

33:52.747 --> 33:54.163
YEAH, NOBODY SUPPOSED
TO DIE LIKE THIS.

33:54.166 --> 33:56.400
NOBODY SUPPOSED TO HAVE
THEIR WORK DESTROYED.

33:56.402 --> 33:57.801
SAM:
TONY,

33:57.803 --> 33:58.802
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO KEEP YOUR HANDS

33:58.804 --> 33:59.803
WHERE WE CAN SEE THEM.

33:59.805 --> 34:02.339
ALEXI?
ALEXI KANISKY?

34:04.676 --> 34:06.209
YOU KNOW WHO I AM.

34:06.211 --> 34:08.412
I KNOW YOU'RE THE ONLY MAN
WHO CAN HELP ME.

34:08.414 --> 34:09.479
WE KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
AT LEWELLEN.

34:09.481 --> 34:10.447
I CAN'T HELP YOU.

34:10.449 --> 34:12.282
YEAH, YOU CAN.

34:12.284 --> 34:13.450
I WON'T HELP YOU.

34:13.452 --> 34:16.286
THEN YOU'RE KILLING
ALL OF US.

34:16.288 --> 34:17.354
THEN WE DIE.

34:25.831 --> 34:28.165
<i> ED:</i>
<i> GENTLY, GENTLY.</i>

34:29.101 --> 34:30.367
WATCH THE LEGS.

34:30.369 --> 34:32.836
OKAY, GENTLE.
GENTLY, GENTLY.

34:34.807 --> 34:36.306
SPIKE:
ALEXI, I NEED TO MAKE SURE
YOU DON'T HAVE ANYTHING

34:36.308 --> 34:37.507
THAT'S GONNA SET OFF
OUR BOMB EARLY.

34:37.509 --> 34:39.309
I WOULD HAVE SET IT OFF
ALREADY.

34:39.311 --> 34:40.827
I DON'T THINK SO.

34:40.828 --> 34:42.344
I THINK YOU WOULD'VE WAITED
UNTIL WE HAD RANIA WAS SAFE.

34:42.347 --> 34:44.347
I DON'T THINK YOU WANTED
TO HURT ANYONE TODAY.

34:44.349 --> 34:45.849
HE'S CLEAN.

34:45.850 --> 34:47.350
GUYS, I REALLY DON'T THINK
WE NEED GUNS DOWN HERE.

34:47.352 --> 34:49.386
<i> YOU CAN'T MAKE THINGS</i>
<i> ANY WORSE.</i>

34:49.388 --> 34:50.654
PARKER:
THAT'S IT, SPIKE,

34:50.656 --> 34:53.256
PEER TO PEER SPIKE,
BUILD THE CONNECTION.

34:54.293 --> 34:56.159
<i>ED:</i>
<i>WE'RE GOOD.</i>

34:57.096 --> 34:58.795
PARAMEDICS ARE TAKING CARE
OF RANIA.

34:58.797 --> 35:00.363
<i>RAF, COMING DOWN TO YOU.</i>

35:00.365 --> 35:02.265
NO, MAN, SAM'S HURT,
HE'S NEXT.

35:02.267 --> 35:03.767
SENIORITY.
I STAY. GET OUTTA HERE.

35:03.769 --> 35:04.768
GUYS, WE DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR THIS,

35:04.770 --> 35:06.203
<i>THE HARNESS IS HERE.</i>

35:06.205 --> 35:07.504
RAF, NOW!

35:07.506 --> 35:08.738
<i> WE ONLY GOT A FEW MINUTES.</i>

35:08.740 --> 35:10.273
I WILL SEE YOU TWO UP TOP.

35:10.275 --> 35:12.242
YUP.

35:12.244 --> 35:14.244
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> SPIKE, TWO MONTHS</i>
<i> AFTER KANISKY LEFT</i>

35:14.246 --> 35:15.745
LEWELLEN STOCK JUMPED.

35:15.747 --> 35:17.814
THEY MADE A BIG ANNOUNCEMENT
ABOUT NEW TECHNOLOGY.

35:17.816 --> 35:19.216
A "BREAKTHROUGH
IN MISSILE CONTROL."

35:19.218 --> 35:21.251
<i> HE DIDN'T SELL</i>
<i> COMPANY SECRETS.</i>

35:21.253 --> 35:23.353
<i> THEY FRAMED HIM</i>
<i> AND THEN FROZE HIM OUT.</i>

35:23.355 --> 35:25.755
<i> RAF:</i>
<i> LET'S GO, ED.</i>

35:25.757 --> 35:27.457
YOU FOUND OUT GALINA WORKED,
DIDN'T YOU?

35:27.459 --> 35:29.526
THOSE FAILURES IN THE FIELD,
THOSE WERE ALL LIES.

35:29.528 --> 35:31.328
YOUR IDEA WAS MAKING
THE COMPANY MILLIONS.

35:31.330 --> 35:32.863
I KEPT TRYING TO PROVE IT
IN COURT.

35:32.865 --> 35:34.397
BUT WHO AM I
TO MEN LIKE THAT?

35:34.399 --> 35:35.765
THEY JUST TOOK IT.

35:35.767 --> 35:37.234
AND THIS IS YOUR WAY
OF TAKING IT BACK.

35:37.236 --> 35:38.635
I GAVE EVERYTHING TO THEM.

35:38.637 --> 35:39.736
WELL THEN,
DON'T GIVE 'EM YOUR LIFE.

35:39.738 --> 35:41.238
TELL ME HOW TO DEFUSE
THE BOMB.

35:41.240 --> 35:43.573
I CAN'T LET THEM WIN.

35:46.712 --> 35:48.712
ED:
LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

35:50.282 --> 35:51.581
(BUCKLES CLICK)

35:52.518 --> 35:54.068
RAF, YOU GOTTA GET BACK.

35:54.069 --> 35:55.619
GUYS,
I NEED THE PLACE EMPTY NOW.

35:55.621 --> 35:57.387
<i> NOW.</i>

35:57.389 --> 35:59.422
YOU GOTTA GO, BUDDY.

36:01.393 --> 36:03.260
SPIKE, WE'RE RUNNING OUT
OF TIME.

36:03.262 --> 36:04.794
AFTER SAM, IT'S YOU.

36:08.634 --> 36:09.833
PARKER:
IF KANISKY DOESN'T GIVE UP
THE CODE,

36:09.835 --> 36:11.301
HE'S NOT GONNA MAKE IT.

36:11.303 --> 36:13.336
I THINK THAT'S
WHAT HE'S GOING FOR.

36:13.338 --> 36:14.838
<i> SPIKE, COME ON.</i>

36:14.840 --> 36:16.439
GO, SEE YOUR DAD.
HE'S NOT GONNA GIVE IT UP.

36:16.441 --> 36:17.641
ERE'S STILL TIME.
SPIKE.

36:17.643 --> 36:19.643
LET ME DO MY JOB, SAM.
YOU'RE NEXT.

36:20.579 --> 36:22.279
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> OKAY.</i>

36:22.281 --> 36:24.281
(HARNESS FASTENERS CLICK)

36:28.787 --> 36:31.388
UH...
I'M SORRY ABOUT YOUR FATHER.

36:34.493 --> 36:36.393
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> ED, LET'S GO.</i>

36:36.395 --> 36:38.261
SEE YOU TOPSIDE.

36:39.198 --> 36:40.463
YOU BETTER.

36:42.568 --> 36:44.467
I KNOW THAT PAIN.

36:44.469 --> 36:45.936
YOUR FATHER?

36:45.937 --> 36:47.404
YEAH, MY MOTHER.
SHE GAVE EVERYTHING TO ME.

36:47.406 --> 36:49.089
YEAH, MY DAD DID TOO.

36:49.090 --> 36:50.773
<i>ALEXI:</i>
<i>WELL, HE MUST BE VERY PROUD.</i>

36:50.776 --> 36:52.375
WHAT'S THE CODE, ALEXI?

36:52.377 --> 36:54.611
WELL, MY MOTHER, SHE DIED
AND EVERYTHING SHE GAVE ME,

36:54.613 --> 36:57.480
ALL OF HER DREAMS,
BRAFT TOOK AWAY.

36:57.482 --> 37:01.785
YOUR MOTHER WOULDN'T WANT
YOU TO DIE FOR THAT.

37:01.787 --> 37:03.286
YOU WOULD DIE
FOR WHAT YOU DO.

37:03.288 --> 37:04.821
TELL ME,
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?

37:04.823 --> 37:07.591
PARKER:
SPIKE, THE SECOND THAT LINE
COMES DOWN YOU'RE IN IT.

37:07.593 --> 37:09.526
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> COPY THAT, BOSS.</i>

37:09.528 --> 37:10.994
YOU EVER BLOW STUFF UP
AS A KID?

37:10.996 --> 37:12.495
SMOKE, VOLCANOES.

37:12.497 --> 37:14.631
BAKING SODA AND VINEGAR.

37:14.633 --> 37:16.533
<i> FOR ME,</i>
<i> IT WAS FIREWORKS.</i>

37:16.535 --> 37:17.968
<i> ROMAN CANDLES,</i>

37:17.970 --> 37:19.369
POLUMNAS.

37:19.371 --> 37:21.438
MY DAD HATED IT.
HE WAS ALWAYS WORRYING.

37:21.440 --> 37:23.674
SAME AS MY MOTHER.

37:23.675 --> 37:25.909
HE FELT MAYBE IT WOULD
TURN ME INTO A SCIENTIST,

37:25.911 --> 37:27.744
A CHEMIST, SOMETHING
HE COULD BE PROUD OF.

37:27.746 --> 37:29.479
SOMETHING SAFE.

37:29.481 --> 37:31.665
ONE DAY, HE CAME HOME

37:31.666 --> 37:33.850
AND HE CAUGHT ME MIXING
CAMPING FUEL, BLEACH...

37:33.852 --> 37:34.951
...CITRIC ACID.

37:34.953 --> 37:37.988
YEAH.
THAT'S A GREAT EXPLOSION.

37:37.990 --> 37:39.890
SPIKE, GET IN THE HARNESS.

37:39.891 --> 37:41.791
SPIKE:
BUT THE THING IS,
I DIDN'T DO IT RIGHT

37:41.793 --> 37:44.361
AND I BURNED MYSELF PRETTY BAD.

37:44.363 --> 37:45.962
I WAS NINE YEARS OLD.

37:45.964 --> 37:48.531
DID YOU STOP MAKING BOMBS
AFTER THAT?

37:48.533 --> 37:50.834
NO. BUT I LEARNED
HOW TO DO IT RIGHT.

37:50.836 --> 37:53.470
AND THEN LATER ON I LEARNED
HOW TO TAKE THEM APART.

37:53.472 --> 37:55.905
BECAUSE I DIDN'T WANNA SEE
PEOPLE TO GET HURT.

37:55.907 --> 37:57.374
I DIDN'T WANT ANYONE
TO SEE THE LOOK I SAW

37:57.376 --> 37:58.475
IN MY DAD'S EYES.

37:58.477 --> 38:00.443
ED:
SPIKE, YOU READY?

38:03.482 --> 38:04.514
SPIKE, YOU READY?

38:04.516 --> 38:05.649
ALMOST.

38:06.818 --> 38:09.286
YOU BUILT A BEAUTIFUL BOMB,
ALEXI.

38:09.288 --> 38:10.453
IT'S PERFECT.

38:10.455 --> 38:11.488
<i> IT'S BEAUTIFUL.</i>

38:11.490 --> 38:12.989
<i> I CAN'T STOP IT.</i>

38:12.991 --> 38:15.058
BUT I DON'T WANNA
SEE YOU DIE.

38:15.060 --> 38:16.693
I HOPE YOUR FATHER
FINDS PEACE.

38:16.695 --> 38:19.062
SPIKE:
YEAH, I HOPE YOU DO TOO.

38:19.064 --> 38:22.432
MAYBE YOU'LL SEE YOUR MOTHER
AGAIN.

38:22.434 --> 38:24.000
WHAT WAS HER NAME?

38:26.338 --> 38:27.404
GALINA.

38:29.474 --> 38:30.940
GALINA.

38:30.942 --> 38:33.543
BOSS, THE CODE IS GALINA.

38:33.545 --> 38:35.578
IT'S ALPHANUMERIC,
LIKE A PHONE.

38:35.580 --> 38:36.713
QUICK, HELP ME OUT.

38:36.714 --> 38:37.847
WHAT WERE THOSE NUMBERS
HE KEYED IN AGAIN?

38:37.849 --> 38:40.550
ALPHA-NUMERIC,
IT'S LIKE A PHONE. G!

38:40.552 --> 38:42.302
PARKER:
BUDDY, BUDDY, BUDDY,
WHAT'RE YOU DOING?

38:42.303 --> 38:44.053
SPIKE:
IF GALINA'S THE CODE
I CAN DISARM THE INFRARED

38:44.056 --> 38:45.455
AND GET RID OF THE DETONATOR.

38:45.457 --> 38:46.456
SPIKE, GET IN THAT HARNESS!

38:46.458 --> 38:47.590
SPIKE:
G! A, B, C,

38:47.592 --> 38:48.591
D, E, F, G!

38:48.593 --> 38:49.659
G IS FOUR.
FOUR!

38:50.595 --> 38:52.562
THERE'S NO TIME,
YOU GET OUTTA THERE!

38:52.564 --> 38:54.497
A! A IS... A'S TWO,
AM I RIGHT?

38:54.499 --> 38:55.498
FOUR, TWO...

38:55.500 --> 38:56.666
L! A, B, C...

38:56.668 --> 38:57.934
